WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.280
[Amit Varma]: A common delusion that many of us suffer from is that the world as we see it is the world

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:11.280
[Amit Varma]: as it is.

00:00:11.280 --> 00:00:16.080
[Amit Varma]: We look around and everything seems clear to us so we assume that everyone else sees

00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:17.320
[Amit Varma]: what we see.

00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:20.280
[Amit Varma]: What is obvious to us should be obvious to them as well.

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:22.920
[Amit Varma]: We get exasperated when it isn't so.

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:26.120
[Amit Varma]: And often we only look at the world through our own eyes.

00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:28.360
[Amit Varma]: That is such a limited way to live.

00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:31.520
[Amit Varma]: This is why I recommend reading as much as we can.

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:36.560
[Amit Varma]: Books allow us to enter the lives of others, to see the world in subtle new ways, to enhance

00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:38.760
[Amit Varma]: our understanding of our own selves.

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:43.640
[Amit Varma]: And that's why, on the seen and the unseen, I love talking to guests about their lives.

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:47.880
[Amit Varma]: How they grew up, what their influences were, the texture of their days.

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:52.160
[Amit Varma]: People as old as me or older lived in a world that had so little of what we take for granted

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:53.160
[Amit Varma]: today.

00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:56.500
[Amit Varma]: All the books and music and cinema of the world were not at our fingertips.

00:00:56.500 --> 00:00:58.640
[Amit Varma]: We did not have the internet at our disposal.

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:02.420
[Amit Varma]: When we had free time, we didn't have smartphones we could look into.

00:01:02.420 --> 00:01:04.400
[Amit Varma]: And India back then was so different.

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:09.080
[Amit Varma]: Look, I'm glad we have progressed as much as we have, but I sometimes feel sad that

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:13.560
[Amit Varma]: there are worlds that we left behind that live only in our memories.

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:16.120
[Amit Varma]: I like to revisit those worlds sometimes.

00:01:16.120 --> 00:01:17.280
[Amit Varma]: Do you?

